{"metadata":{"title":"Build a Calculator with Cambium","category":"Cambium","estimatedTime":"4hr 50min","role":"overview","categoryPathComponent":"TableOfContents"},"hierarchy":{"reference":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents","paths":[]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"overview","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/tutorials\/tableofcontents"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[{"kind":"hero","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium is a Swift-native concrete syntax tree library. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tutorial series walks you through building a small but","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"production-shaped calculator language end-to-end: a recursive-","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"descent parser that produces a lossless tree, a typed AST overlay,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an evaluator with memoized analysis, persistent edits with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identity-preserving witnesses, an incremental reparse loop, fork-","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"join evaluation across structured-concurrent tasks, parallel","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parsing with externalized interning, and on-disk serialization.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each chapter culminates in REPL commands you can try in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"companion sample at "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Examples\/Calculator"},{"type":"text","text":". By the end you will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have built the same library that backs the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"calc-repl"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"executable, one Cambium subsystem at a time."}]}],"title":"Build a Calculator with Cambium","action":{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Get started","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Get started","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/01-DefineLanguage"}},{"kind":"volume","name":null,"image":null,"content":[],"chapters":[{"image":"chapter-banner.png","name":"Build a Lossless CST","tutorials":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/01-DefineLanguage","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/02-DriveBuilder","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/03-PrecedenceAndRecovery"],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium represents a parsed document as a homogeneous green tree"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whose nodes are tagged with a kind. In this chapter you define the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calculator’s grammar, drive a builder from a recursive-descent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parser, and add Pratt-style precedence and parser-level error"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recovery so the resulting tree round-trips even malformed input."}]}]},{"image":"chapter-banner.png","name":"Read and Model the Tree","tutorials":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/04-ReadingTree","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/05-TypedAST","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/06-Evaluator"],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once a tree exists, consumers need to walk it, query it by byte"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"position, and project a typed view for kind-specific work. This"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"chapter introduces borrowed cursors, owned handles, byte-streaming"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text reads, and a typed AST overlay generated from the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumSyntaxMacros\/CambiumSyntaxNode(_:for:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" macro, then uses"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"them to build a recursive evaluator."}]}]},{"image":"chapter-banner.png","name":"Edit, Reparse, and Memoize","tutorials":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/07-ReplacementWitnesses","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/08-IncrementalReparse","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/09-AnalysisTranslation"],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium’s trees are persistent: editing produces a new tree"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sharing as much green storage as possible, with a witness"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"describing the structural change. This chapter wires up constant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"folding via subtree replacement, an incremental reparse loop with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a reuse oracle, and memoized analysis caches whose entries"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"survive edits by translating through the witnesses."}]}]},{"image":"chapter-banner.png","name":"Concurrency and Persistence","tutorials":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/10-ForkJoinEval","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/11-ParallelParse","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/12-Serialization"],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium’s trees promote into "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"snapshots that are "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":" and safe to share across tasks. In"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this chapter you write a structured-concurrent fork-join"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"evaluator, parse a workload of expressions in parallel through a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shared token interner, and serialize a tree to disk for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"editor-style warm restarts."}]}]}]},{"kind":"resources","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reference material that complements the hands-on tutorials."}]}],"tiles":[{"action":{"title":"View more","destination":"https:\/\/xn--wxa.dog\/cambium\/documentation\/cambium\/","type":"link"},"title":"Documentation","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Articles in the Cambium documentation that complement the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"hands-on path:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"“Getting Started” — narrative skim of the API.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"“Calculator” — sample-code overview.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"“Externalized Interning” — deep dive on ","type":"text"},{"code":"TokenInterner","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"identifier":"documentation"},{"action":{"title":"View more","destination":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/tree\/main\/Examples\/Calculator","type":"link"},"title":"Sample Code","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The calculator example is a standalone SwiftPM package at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Examples\/Calculator"},{"type":"text","text":". Each tutorial cites the file in that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example whose canonical implementation it builds toward —"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"read them side by side once you have finished the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"corresponding tutorial."}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/tree\/main\/Examples\/Calculator","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" — the full sample.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/blob\/main\/Examples\/Calculator\/README.md","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" — REPL command reference.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"identifier":"sampleCode"}]}],"references":{"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/01-DefineLanguage":{"title":"Define the Calculator Language","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Every Cambium grammar starts with a kind enumeration: one case per"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"token and one per node the parser can produce. The kind enum"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"becomes the "},{"code":"Kind","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" associated type of a "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conformance, and Cambium specializes its generic types around that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"language to make tree storage compact and traversal type-safe."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/01-definelanguage","role":"project","estimatedTime":"15min","kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/01-DefineLanguage"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/12-Serialization":{"title":"Save and Load Trees","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium can serialize a tree to a compact byte stream and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"decode it back. The format is length-, hash-, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"kind-validated at every record, so flipped bytes produce"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"named errors at decode time rather than silently malformed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"trees."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/12-serialization","role":"project","estimatedTime":"15min","kind":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/12-Serialization","type":"topic"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/10-ForkJoinEval":{"role":"project","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":". Cambium’s red"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"layer realizes lazily under lock-free atomic slots, so two"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tasks descending into different siblings of the same parent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"never observe inconsistent state. The typed AST overlays are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"also ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sendable, Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", so passing a sub-expression to a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"child task is just an argument pass."}],"kind":"project","title":"Fork-Join Evaluation Across Tasks","type":"topic","estimatedTime":"25min","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/10-ForkJoinEval","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/10-forkjoineval"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/09-AnalysisTranslation":{"role":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The witnesses you built in Tutorial 7 (replacement) and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Tutorial 8 (reparse) exist to make analysis caches "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"survive","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"edits"}]},{"type":"text","text":". Without translation every keystroke would invalidate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"every memoized value — defeating the whole point of an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"incremental tool."}],"kind":"project","title":"Translate Analysis Across Edits","type":"topic","estimatedTime":"30min","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/09-AnalysisTranslation","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/09-analysistranslation"},"chapter-banner.png":{"alt":"Chapter banner","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/org.cambium.Cambium\/chapter-banner.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"chapter-banner.png","type":"image"},"https://github.com/daig/cambium/tree/main/Examples/Calculator":{"title":"Examples\/Calculator","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/tree\/main\/Examples\/Calculator","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Examples\/Calculator"}],"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/tree\/main\/Examples\/Calculator"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/05-TypedAST":{"title":"Project a Typed AST Overlay","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium’s CST stores everything as homogeneous nodes tagged"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a kind. That uniformity is what makes editing and reuse"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cheap, but it leaves consumers to write "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"switch node.kind { ... }"},{"type":"text","text":" everywhere they want kind-specific behavior."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/05-typedast","role":"project","estimatedTime":"25min","kind":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/05-TypedAST","type":"topic"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/documentation/CambiumIncremental":{"url":"\/documentation\/cambiumincremental","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumIncremental","kind":"symbol","title":"CambiumIncremental","role":"collection","type":"topic"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/04-ReadingTree":{"title":"Read the Tree Without Allocating","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Cambium tree is meant to be queried frequently — by IDEs on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"every keystroke, by analyzers walking every node, by formatters"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"emitting bytes. To stay within reasonable memory and ARC"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"budgets the primary traversal API is borrowed: walks happen"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"~Copyable"},{"type":"text","text":" cursors handed to a closure, and source"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text is exposed as a chunk-streaming view rather than a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"materialized "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/04-readingtree","role":"project","estimatedTime":"25min","kind":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/04-ReadingTree","type":"topic"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/02-DriveBuilder":{"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/02-drivebuilder","estimatedTime":"25min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"With the kind enum in place, you can write a recursive-descent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parser that emits into a "},{"code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"builder accepts a stream of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"startNode"},{"text":" \/ ","type":"text"},{"code":"token","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" \/ ","type":"text"},{"code":"staticToken","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"\/ "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"finishNode"},{"type":"text","text":" calls and produces a green tree whose structure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"mirrors the calls one-for-one.","type":"text"}],"kind":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/02-DriveBuilder","title":"Drive a GreenTreeBuilder","role":"project","type":"topic"},"https://github.com/daig/cambium/blob/main/Examples/Calculator/README.md":{"title":"README.md","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/blob\/main\/Examples\/Calculator\/README.md","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"README.md"}],"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/blob\/main\/Examples\/Calculator\/README.md"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/03-PrecedenceAndRecovery":{"role":"project","abstract":[{"text":"The parser from the previous tutorial handles only “atomic”","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"prefix forms — literals and parenthesized groups. To parse"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"1 + 2 * 3","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" correctly the parser needs operator precedence; to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"survive ","type":"text"},{"code":"1 +","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"(2","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" it needs error recovery.","type":"text"}],"kind":"project","title":"Add Precedence and Error Recovery","type":"topic","estimatedTime":"30min","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/03-PrecedenceAndRecovery","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/03-precedenceandrecovery"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/06-Evaluator":{"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/06-evaluator","estimatedTime":"20min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"With the typed AST in place from Tutorial 5, an evaluator"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"becomes a recursive function that pattern-matches on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ExprSyntax"},{"type":"text","text":". Each kind has a closed structure — its operands"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and operator are addressable through the typed accessors —"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so the evaluator stays small and total."}],"kind":"project","title":"Evaluate the Typed AST","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/06-Evaluator","role":"project","type":"topic"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/08-IncrementalReparse":{"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/08-incrementalreparse","estimatedTime":"30min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An IDE re-runs the parser on every keystroke. Reparsing the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whole document each time is wasteful when most subtrees did"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not change. "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumIncremental","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" exposes the four pieces"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you wire together for "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"subtree-level","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" reuse:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/IncrementalParseSession"},{"type":"text","text":" (long-lived"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"bookkeeping), "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ReuseOracle"},{"type":"text","text":" (the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parser-facing query API), "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/TextEdit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the change description), and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseWitness"},{"type":"text","text":" (the post-parse summary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of what was reused)."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/08-IncrementalReparse","title":"Incrementally Reparse","kind":"project","role":"project","type":"topic"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/11-ParallelParse":{"kind":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Parallel parsing splits work across worker tasks: each"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"worker parses an independent subtree concurrently, then a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"master builder splices the worker results into one logical"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tree. The correctness-critical question is how the workers","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"share token-text vocabulary and the green-node namespace.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/11-parallelparse","role":"project","type":"topic","title":"Parallel Parsing with Shared Interning","estimatedTime":"25min","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/11-ParallelParse"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/documentation/CambiumSyntaxMacros/CambiumSyntaxNode(_:for:)":{"title":"CambiumSyntaxNode(_:for:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Generate the standard stored syntax handle and unchecked initializer for a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"concrete typed syntax-node wrapper."}],"url":"\/documentation\/cambiumsyntaxmacros\/cambiumsyntaxnode(_:for:)","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"macro","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CambiumSyntaxNode","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Kind","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"Kind","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:19CambiumSyntaxMacros4KindL_xmfp"},{"text":".Type, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"for","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Kind","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:19CambiumSyntaxMacros4KindL_xmfp"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumSyntaxMacros\/CambiumSyntaxNode(_:for:)","type":"topic"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/07-ReplacementWitnesses":{"title":"Replace Subtrees with Witnesses","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium trees are persistent: there is no in-place mutation."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SharedSyntaxTree.replacing(_:with:context:)"},{"type":"text","text":" produces a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"new","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tree that shares as much green storage with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the old as possible, and returns a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementWitness","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" describing the structural"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"change."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/07-ReplacementWitnesses","role":"project","estimatedTime":"25min","kind":"project","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/07-replacementwitnesses"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/TableOfContents":{"kind":"overview","abstract":[{"text":"Cambium is a Swift-native concrete syntax tree library. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tutorial series walks you through building a small but"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"production-shaped calculator language end-to-end: a recursive-"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"descent parser that produces a lossless tree, a typed AST overlay,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"an evaluator with memoized analysis, persistent edits with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"identity-preserving witnesses, an incremental reparse loop, fork-"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"join evaluation across structured-concurrent tasks, parallel"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"parsing with externalized interning, and on-disk serialization."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/tableofcontents","role":"overview","type":"topic","title":"Build a Calculator with Cambium","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents"}}}